    "Thus after going through the same argument as above, we can further extend the ψ n -reality theorem to the indexed wavefunction coefficients with m massless scalars and n -m massless gravitons:Im ψ m;(i 1 i 2)•••(j 1 j 2) n-m = 0, 0 ≤ m ≤ n. (4.22)• We can also consider conformally-coupled scalars φ on the external lines where the bulk-boundary propagators areK φ (η, k) = η η 0 e ik(η-η 0), (4.23)where the η 0 -dependence ensures that we satisfy the future boundary condition.",
    "Clearly this propagator is not real after Wick rotation, instead it is purely imaginary.",
    "Our reality theorem then extends to these fields if we have an even number of them on external lines.• The ψ n -reality automatically implies the reality of the total-energy k T -singularities within.",
